{"lemma":"قَعِيدَيْ","slug":"قَعِيدَيْ","root":"ق.ع.د","root_slug":"ق-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَعِيد","root":"قعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35963"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35963","headword_ar":"قَعِيدٌ","root":"qEd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A companion in sitting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, AHeyth, L, K:) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaAEilN","text_ar":"مُفَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A preserver; a keeper; a guardian; a watcher."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) [In some copies of the K, by the omission of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this meaning is assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqaAEidN","text_ar":"مُقَاعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] It is used alike as sing. and pl. and masc. and fem. (L, K) and dual also. (L.) It is said in the Kur, [l. 16,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani","text_ar":"عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyamiyni waEani Al$imaAli qaEiydN","text_ar":"اليَمِينِ وَعَنِ الشِمَالِ قَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On the right and on the left a sitter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guardian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watcher"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: respecting which it is observed, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are of the measures used alike as sing. and dual and pl.; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aA rasuwlu rab~ika","text_ar":"اـِنَّا رَسُولُ رَبِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [Kur xi. 83, accord. to one reading,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlmalaAy^ikapu baEoda *`lika ZahiyrN","text_ar":"وَالمَلَايِكَةُ بَعْدَ ذٰلِكَ ظَهِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [Kur lxvi. 4:] (S, L:) or, as the grammarians say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydN","text_ar":"قَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is understood after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alymyn","text_ar":"اليمين"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A father;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydapN","text_ar":"قَعِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEaAdN","text_ar":"قِعَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydapu bayoti rajulK","text_ar":"قَعِيدَةُ بَيْتِ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man's wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEaAy^idu","text_ar":"قَعَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEodaka","text_ar":"قَعْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but the last was unknown to AHeyth, (L,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeper, God:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEyd","text_ar":"قعيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEd","text_ar":"قعد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"being epithets, put in the acc. case because of the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"understood: or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I conjure thee by God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$adotuka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"نَشَدْتُكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": some say, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though God were sitting with thee, watching over thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keeping thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in some copies of the K, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHifoZihi Ealayoka","text_ar":"بِحِفْظِهِ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading in the TA, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHofaZuhu Ealayoka","text_ar":"يَحْفَظُهُ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy Companion, who is the Companion of every secret,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God"},{"kind":"text","text":"] !"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka laA A=tiyka","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ لَا ا=تِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA Atyk","text_ar":"لا اتيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha lA Atyk","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ لا اتيك"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha lA Atyk","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ لا اتيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; are forms of swearing used by the Arabs, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEyd","text_ar":"قعيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEd","text_ar":"قعد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are inf. us. put in the acc. case because of a verb understood; [or rather, as it appears to me, and as I have said above, they are epithets, put in the acc. case because of the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"understood;] and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy Companion, who is the Companion of every secret,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy Companion, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeper, God, I will not come to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$adotuka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"نَشَدْتُكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:) some say, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEyd","text_ar":"قعيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEd","text_ar":"قعد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify here a watcher, or an observer, and a preserver, a keeper, or a guardian, that God is meant by them, and that they are in the acc. case because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uqosimu","text_ar":"اُقْسِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"followed by the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is understood; [the meaning being I swear"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeper, &c., God, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this opinion is the more agreeable with the explanation given above, “ By thy Companion &c. ”:] others say, that they are inf. ns., and that the meaning is, I swear"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy regard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, of God,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimuraAqabatika A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"بِمُرَاقَبَتِكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": El-Mázinee and others, however, assert that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEyd","text_ar":"قعيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"has no verb. (MF.) ―         -b5-  Ks says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~`h","text_ar":"اللّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":"being in the nom. case] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God be with thee!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God be thy Companion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeper!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and so does"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka All~`hu","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ اللّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHeyth, L.) [Or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB, L, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEodaka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعْدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB, L, TA,) [are] expressions of conciliation, not oaths, as they have not the complement of an oath: the former word in each is an inf. n. occupying the place of a verb, and therefore is put in the acc. case, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamoraka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"عَمْرَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~arotuka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"عَمَّرْتُكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., I beg God to prolong thy life: in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaE~adotuka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعَّدْتُكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiEodaka","text_ar":"قِعْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies, [and so the three first phrases above, of which it is the original form,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I beg God to preserve, keep, guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watch, thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the saying in the Kur, [l. 16,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Alyamiyni","text_ar":"عَنِ اليَمِينِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEani Al$~imaAli qaEiydN","text_ar":"وَعَنِ الشِّمَالِ قَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyZN","text_ar":"حَفِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Aboo-'Alee, IB, L, K. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiyda kumaA A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعِيدَ كُمَا ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in interrogative phrases and in phrases conveying an oath, [and so is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2547},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say, interrogatively,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEibdakumaA","text_ar":"قَعِبدَكُمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha A^alamo yakuno ka*aA waka*aA","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ اَلَمْ يَكُنْ كَذَا وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I beg God to preserve, keep, guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watch, thee. Was it not so and so?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in the other case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka A@ll~`ha laA^ukoriman~aka","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ ا@للّٰهَ لَاُكْرِمَنَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keeper, God, I will assuredly pay thee honour!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Th, L.) ―         -b6-  [And from the signification of ' father ' is derived] the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEiydaka latafoEalan~a","text_ar":"قَعِيدَكَ لَتَفْعَلَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy father, thou shalt assuredly do"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing. (K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What comes to thee from behind thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gazelles"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild animals: contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naTyHN","text_ar":"نَطيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of evil omen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A3-  The locust"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the wings are not yet perfectly formed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","AHeyth","L","K","IB","TA"]}]}}